<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="177" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1506,1855]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1455889530" country="Japan" location="Red Sea" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Red Sea">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1542,1567]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on one mature specimen. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pritchard" box="[1040,1241,1542,1567]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Pritchard, M. H. (1966 a) A revision of the genus Podocotyle (Trematoda Opecoelidae). Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 93, 158 - 172." type="journal article" year="1966" yearSuffix="a">Pritchard (1966a)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,319,1578,1603]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Apopodocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,319,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Apopodocotyle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb" box="[384,549,1578,1603]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Cribb, T. H. (2005 a) Family Opecoelidae Ozaki, 1925. In: Jones, A., Bray, R. A. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (Eds), Keys to the Trematoda. Fol. 2. CABI Publishing and The Natural History Museum, Wallingford, pp. 443 - 531." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="a">Cribb (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
returned it to 
<taxonomicName box="[738,911,1578,1603]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Hamacreadium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[738,911,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Hamacreadium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when he synonymised 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1372,1578,1603]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Apopodocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1372,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Apopodocotyle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,324,1614,1639]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Cainocreadium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,324,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Cainocreadium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It does not belong in 
<taxonomicName box="[572,745,1614,1639]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Hamacreadium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[572,745,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Hamacreadium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the vitelline follicles are restricted to the hindbody. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Yamaguti, 1942) Pritchard, 1966" authorityName="(Yamaguti, 1942) Pritchard" authorityYear="1966" box="[270,912,1650,1675]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Allopodocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="lethrini">
<emphasis box="[270,529,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Allopodocotyle lethrini</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguti" box="[544,724,1650,1675]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Yamaguti, S. (1942) Studies on the helminth fauna of Japan. Part 39. Trematodes of fishes mainly from Naha. Transactions of the Biogeographical Society of Japan, 3, 329 - 399." type="journal article" year="1942">Yamaguti, 1942</bibRefCitation>
) Pritchard, 1966
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Yamaguti, 1942) Pritchard, 1966" authorityName="(Yamaguti, 1942) Pritchard" authorityYear="1966" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Allopodocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="tamame">
<emphasis box="[967,1233,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Allopodocotyle tamame</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguti" box="[1247,1428,1650,1675]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Yamaguti, S. (1942) Studies on the helminth fauna of Japan. Part 39. Trematodes of fishes mainly from Naha. Transactions of the Biogeographical Society of Japan, 3, 329 - 399." type="journal article" year="1942">Yamaguti, 1942</bibRefCitation>
) Pritchard, 1966
</taxonomicName>
, which are parasites of lethrinids from off 
<collectingCountry box="[798,865,1687,1710]" name="Japan" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Japan</collectingCountry>
, but 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1086,1686,1711]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Allopodocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[917,1086,1686,1711]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Allopodocotyle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are characterised by an entire ovary, whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagaty" box="[405,571,1723,1747]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Nagaty, H. F. (1941) Trematodes of fishes from the Red Sea. II. The genus Hamacreadium Linton, 1910 (Family Allocreadiidae) with a description of two new species. The Journal of the Egyptian Medical Association, 24, 300 - 310." type="journal article" year="1941">Nagaty (1941)</bibRefCitation>
described a four-lobed ovary. The condition of the ovary and the vitelline follicles suggest it belongs in 
<taxonomicName box="[502,628,1758,1783]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Podocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,628,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Podocotyle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pritchard" box="[646,833,1758,1783]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Pritchard, M. H. (1966 a) A revision of the genus Podocotyle (Trematoda Opecoelidae). Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 93, 158 - 172." type="journal article" year="1966" yearSuffix="a">Pritchard 1966a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibson" box="[848,1095,1758,1783]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Gibson, D. I. &amp; Bray, R. A. (1982) A study and reorganization of Plagioporus Stafford, 1904 (Digenea: Opecoelidae) and related genera, with special reference to forms from European Atlantic waters. Journal of Natural History, 16, 529 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938200770431" type="journal article" year="1982">Gibson &amp; Bray 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb" box="[1110,1257,1758,1783]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Cribb, T. H. (2005 a) Family Opecoelidae Ozaki, 1925. In: Jones, A., Bray, R. A. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (Eds), Keys to the Trematoda. Fol. 2. CABI Publishing and The Natural History Museum, Wallingford, pp. 443 - 531." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="a">Cribb 2005a</bibRefCitation>
), to which it is transferred here. It resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[487,605,1794,1819]" class="Trematoda" family="Opecoelidae" genus="Podocotyle" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="bongosi">
<emphasis box="[487,501,1796,1819]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[516,605,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">bongosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also from the 
<collectingRegion box="[777,869,1794,1819]" country="Egypt" name="Al Bahr al Ahmar" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Red Sea</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nagaty" box="[885,1201,1794,1819]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refString="Nagaty, H. F. &amp; Abdel Aal, T. M. (1962 b) Trematodes of fishes from the Red Sea. 19. On three new species of Podocotyle (family Allocreadiidae). The Journal of Parasitology, 48, 746 - 747." type="journal article" year="1962" yearSuffix="b">Nagaty &amp; Abdel Aal 1962b</bibRefCitation>
) but that species has an extra-caecal genital pore.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
